description: After an encounter with the Hitman Team's Formaggio, Narancia hunts down his assailant with a hail of bullets as Formaggio tries to understand his attacker's tracking skills.
title: Hitman Team

description: Narancia is unshakable as he uses firepower and CO2 detection to survive Formaggio's body-shrinking attack.
title: Narancia's Li'l Bomber

description: Giorno, Abbacchio and Fugo travel to Pompeii to find a hidden key pivotal in their protection of Trish. Facing the trio, however, is more than the lonely remains of ancient Roman villas and colonnades.

input: The Second Mission From the Boss

title: The Second Mission From the Boss

description: Amid the gritty beauty of Napoli, the Joestar lineage lives on. After sidestepping long-term Joestar ally Koichi Hirose, Giorno must contend with two powerful Mafia gangsters, Leaky Eye Lucca and the enigmatic Bruno Bucciarati.
title: Golden Wind

description: Eager to identify Leaky Eye Luca's attacker, Bucciarati confronts Giorno and unleashes a Stand attack to dismantle him piece by piece. But Giorno counters with his Stand Golden Wind, surprising not just his adversary, but also himself.
title: Bucciarati Appears

description: Determined to join the mafia gang Passione, altruistic Giorno is introduced by Bucciarati to the grotesquely corpulent Polpo, an incarcerated capo who tests Giorno's loyalty with a simple but bizarrely lethal test.

input: Meet the Mafioso Behind the Wall

title: Meet the Mafioso Behind the Wall

description: Plodding amid the dusky shadows of a peaceful piazza is Polpo's macabre Stand, which assails any who dare witness the reigniting of the lighter. Giorno deciphers its method of attack, but is soon staring death in the face.
title: Joining the Famiglia

description: Take an Italian adventure with this brand new season of JoJo’s Bizarre Adventure: Golden Wind, premiering this Saturday night at 2:30a!
title: Jojo Golden Wind Trailer

description: While word of the high-ranking capo Polpo's alleged suicide sparks astonishment and speculation in the crime syndicate Passione, Giorno is inducted into Bucciarati's eclectic mafia family.
title: Find Polpo's Fortune!

description: Sailing to the Isle of Capri to recover Polpo's estate, Bucciarati and team are ambushed by a stealthy enemy Stand that deflates them into rubber-like human pelts.
title: Moody Jazz's Counterattack

description: Having beheaded their captor by zipper, the team learns its plan has been leaked to Zucchero's cohort, who is lying in wait on Capri. With fish and gun, Giorno and Mista swim to beat the boat and weed out their assassin-in-waiting.
title: Six Bullets Appears Part 1

description: As Mista closes in on Sale, all signs seem to point to an easy kill.
title: Six Bullets Appears Part 2

description: Within arm's reach of Polpo's fortune, Bucciarati and team meet the unassuming Pericolo, a capo who has come to accept the treasure.

input: The First Mission From the Boss

title: The First Mission From the Boss

description: Jotaro Kujo travels to a town in Japan called Morioh to find a young man named Josuke Higashikata, the secret love child of his grandfather, Joseph Joestar. Upon finding him, Jotaro is surprised to learn that Josuke also possesses a Stand.
title: Jotaro Kujo! Meets Josuke Higashikata

description: Josuke informs Jotaro about his encounter with Angelo's Stand. Deducing that the serial killer's Stand is capable of entering people's bodies Jotaro tells Josuke over the phone to stay on high alert until he arrives at his home.
title: Josuke Higashikata! Meets Angelo

description: Koichi finds himself blackmailed by a man named Tamami Kobayashi who frames him for running over a cat. Unable to comprehend the situation a panicked Koichi starts to feel guilt for his actions when a giant lock appears on his chest!
title: Koichi Hirose (Reverb)

description: Josuke and Jotaro learn that a man with a bow and arrow was responsible for awakening Angelo's Stand ability. Realizing the town is still in danger, they decide to find the bow and arrow before it can create any more victims.
title: The Nijimura Brothers Part 1

description: Josuke enters the Nijimura Brothers' house to rescue Koichi, who is in critical condition after getting shot by Keicho Nijimura's bow and arrow. But when Josuke steps into the house, he is attacked by Keicho's Stand.
title: The Nijimura Brothers Part 2

description: Koichi is both surprised and excited when a girl named Yukako Yamagishi says she likes him. But Koichi's joy quickly turns into fear after Yukako begins to express her love for him in very erratic and dangerous ways.

input: Yukako Yamagishi Falls in Love Part 1

title: Yukako Yamagishi Falls in Love Part 1

description: Josuke and Koichi are informed that a student at their school may be a Stand user and decide to look into the case. Their suspicions are quickly confirmed after Hazamada's wooden doll suddenly morphs into an exact look-alike of Josuke.
title: Toshikazu Hazamada (Show Off)

description: Koichi insists that they go find the bow and arrow and destroy it so it won't create any more victims and Josuke agrees. When the two enter the attic where the bow and arrow are being kept they hear an inhuman noise.
title: The Nijimura Brothers Part 3

description: Yukako's dangerous obsession with reshaping Koichi into a man fit for her gets worse prompting Koichi to hatch an escape plan. He tries to call Josuke for help using a nearby pay phone but is stopped by Yukako who anticipated his move.

input: Yukako Yamagishi Falls in Love Part 2

title: Yukako Yamagishi Falls in Love Part 2

description: Josuke and Okuyasu come across an Italian restaurant owned by an Italian chef named Tonio. When Okuyasu asks for the menu Tonio explains that he decides the menu on the spot based on the customer he sees.

input: Let's Go Eat Some Italian Food

title: Let's Go Eat Some Italian Food

description: Josuke and his friends gather at Morioh Port to try and reach Joseph Joestar's ship before Chili Pepper. Speculating that the enemy is hiding somewhere nearby Jotaro  and Okuyasu go to protect Joseph.
title: Chili Pepper Part 2

description: Chili Pepper suddenly appears before Josuke to test his Stand powers. Josuke puts up a fight but is overwhelmed by Chili Pepper's speed and power. Then Josuke and his friends learn from Jotaro of a man who can locate Chili Pepper.
title: Chili Pepper Part 1

description: With Akira Otoishi arrested and the bow and arrow safely recovered peace seemingly returns to Morioh Town. But Josuke's life is far from peaceful as he struggles to deal with his father Joseph making things difficult to bond.
title: We Picked Up Something Crazy!

description: Koichi finds himself being drawn back to Rohan's house where he sees the manga artist finishing up his next manga chapter at an incredible speed. Rohan uses his stand Heaven's Door on Koichi to gain further creative inspiration.

input: Let's Go to the Manga Artist's House Part 2
Go to the Manga Artist's House Part 2
to the Manga Artist's House Part 2

title: Let's Go to the Manga Artist's House Part 2

description: Jotaro and Josuke must hunt down a rat that is believed to have become a Stand user after being shot by the bow and arrow. When the two arrive at the site they find dozens of dead rats killed in the most bizarre fashion.
title: Let's Go Hunting!

description: Koichi and Hazamada visit the home of Rohan Kishibe, a popular manga artist whom they are huge fans of. Much to their joy Rohan not only agrees to sign autographs but also invites them to take a tour of his workspace.

input: Let's Go to the Manga Artist's House Part 1
Go to the Manga Artist's House Part 1
to the Manga Artist's House Part 1

title: Let's Go to the Manga Artist's House Part 1

description: Koichi and Rohan discover a small alley that does not appear anywhere on the map. They see where it leads but are unable to get out. Just as Rohan begins to suspect this of being the work of a Stand user a mysterious girl appears.
title: Rohan Kishibe's Adventure

description: Josuke and Okuyasu become friends with a Stand user named Shigechi who can use his Stand to find and collect the money scattered across town. Josuke comes up with an idea using Shigechi's Stand to make a little extra cash for themselves.
title: Shigechi's Harvest Part 1

description: Josuke and friends go to the bank to cash in on the winning lottery ticket they found by using Shigechi's Stand Harvest. The bank clerk is not convinced by their story that they are the actual owners of the ticket.
title: Shigechi's Harvest Part 2

description: Yukako is depressed she can't get Koichi to return her feelings. Yukako comes across a beauty salon where the owner claims that her beauty treatment help customers find love and happiness and decides to give the treatment a try.
title: Yukako Yamagishi Dreams of Cinderella

description: Yoshikage Kira peaceful afternoon is cut short when Shigechi accidentally takes Kira's sandwich bag believing it to be his own. Not wanting anyone to see the object he had placed inside the bag Kira goes after Shigechi to recover it.

input: Yoshikage Kira Just Wants to Live Quietly Part 1
Kira Just Wants to Live Quietly Part 1
Just Wants to Live Quietly Part 1

title: Yoshikage Kira Just Wants to Live Quietly Part 1

description: Yoshikage Kira is revealed to be the serial killer who's been lurking in Morioh Town and a Stand user. Having discovered his secret Shigechi tries to fight off Kira only to suffer fatal wounds from the killer's Stand Deadly Queen.

input: Yoshikage Kira Just Wants to Live Quietly Part 2
Kira Just Wants to Live Quietly Part 2
Just Wants to Live Quietly Part 2

title: Yoshikage Kira Just Wants to Live Quietly Part 2

description: Jotaro and Koichi come under the attack of Yoshikage Kira's Stand bomb called Heart Attack. Narrowly escaping the blast Koichi tries to go after the serial killer but is stopped by Jotaro.
title: Heart Attack Part 1

description: Kira is forced to appear before Koichi after his remote Heart Attack bomb is made useless by the boy's new Stand Reverb Act 3. Finally coming face-to-face with the serial killer Koichi attacks him with Act 3.
title: Heart Attack Part 2

description: Josuke and his friends are at Yoshikage Kira's home trying to find any clues that may lead them to the serial killer who has gone into hiding under a new face and identity.
title: Heart Father

description: Josuke and Okuyasu find a young man lying unconscious in the middle of what appears to be a crop circle.  When they try to take a closer look the man suddenly wakes up and starts claiming he's an alien from outer space.
title: I'm an Alien

description: Rohan is convinced that Josuke is cheating in their game of Cee-lo when all the dice rolls in his opponent's favor. Feeling insulted Rohan stabs his own finger and swear he'll find out how Josuke is cheating in their next round.
title: Highway Go Go Part 1

description: Kira's father begins searching for Stand users who would help protect his son from his pursuers. Meanwhile Rohan is taking photos at the train station when he is suddenly challenged to a game by a boy claiming to be his fan.
title: Rosham Boy is Here!

description: Rohan sacrifices himself to save Josuke from a remote-controlled Stand that sucks nutrients out of its victims. Moved by Rohan's act of bravery Josuke races through town to find and defeat the Stand's user before it can kill Rohan.
title: Highway Go Go Part 2

description: Shinobu tells Kosaku that she saw a stray cat with a hole in its throat. When Kosaku goes to take a look he finds the cat already dead and buries it. The next morning a strange plant sprouts from the spot where the cat was buried.
title: Cats Love Yoshikage Kira

description: Josuke enters the electrical tower again to save Mikitaka and defeat Toyohiro Kanedaichi. Meanwhile Rohan receives a visit from a first-class architect named Masazo Kinoto who's come to estimate the repair costs to his burnt house.
title: July 15th (Thurs) Part 2

description: Yoshihiro Kira spots Kosaku Kawajiri and instantly recognizes that it's actually his son Yoshikage. Meanwhile Josuke, Okuyasu, and Mikitaka finds a strange man living in an abandoned electrical tower.
title: July 15th (Thurs) Part 1

description: Rohan finds himself possessed by Masazo Kinoto's Stand Cheap Trap, who tells the manga artist to burn the photos he took of the people in Morioh. Meanwhile Josuke and Yuya encounter the Stand user responsible for Koichi's disappearance.
title: July 15th (Thurs) Part 3

description: Rohan calls over Koichi to help him fight off Cheap Trap. Unfortunately Koichi thinks Rohan is pulling a prank on him and leaves. Feeling humiliated by Cheap Trap a furious Rohan decides to leave the house to seek other help.
title: July 15th (Thurs) Part 4

description: Kosaku Kawajiri is forced to kill Hayato and learns from his father that Rohan and the others are coming to investigate the Kawajiri family. A desperate Kosaku tries to find a way to escape his situation.
title: Bites the Dust Part 1

description: Yoshikage Kira gains a new ability called Bites the Dust. Realizing that the only people who could stop Kira are ones with similar powers Hayato tries to warn Rohan Kishibe and the others about Kira without revealing his identity.
title: Bites the Dust Part 2

description: Kira realizes that letting Hayato repeat the same morning is becoming a risk so he decides to undo Bites the Dust after he sees through Rohan's death. But just as Kira confirms his victory an unexpected person appears.
title: Shining D (Diamond) Is Unbreakable Part 1

description: Josuke and Hayato hide inside a nearby residence to escape from Deadly Queen and Stray Cat's attack. But to their horror Kira is somehow able to close in on them from outside the house.
title: Shining D (Diamond) Is Unbreakable Part 2

description: Josuke and his friends have finally cornered Yoshikage Kira. Refusing to give up Kira tries to activate Bites the Dust to escape his desperate situation. Can Josuke and the others stop Kira in time to save the future of Morioh?

input: Goodbye, Morioh - The Heart of Gold

title: Goodbye, Morioh - The Heart of Gold

description: Illuso has pulled Fugo into his mirror world as Abbacchio rushes to retrieve the key, despite Giorno's stern advice. But Abbacchio cannot escape a similar fate, leaving him and later Giorno to resort to self-mutilation.
title: Mirror Man and Purple Smoke
